Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery neck-amphora; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of four equine hind legs to left, overlapped by diagonally set staffs or the like; at left edge possibly a further leg, or drapery; narrow black groundline.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 237, no. B108)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0025) (Phase 1)
